<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-06T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-06T18:36:00-05:00" n="1200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1200">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115R39/54</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guaymas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-06T17:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Yaqui Indians attacked Esperanza to-day burning headquarters Richardson
                            Construction Company. Indians are still in valley. General Mange leaving
                            from here with four hundred soldiers this afternoon. Endeavor restore
                            order. About thirty Americans known to be in valley. No details of
                            fighting. Nothing known yet of welfare House in battle. Letter from
                            auditor Richardson Company says nothing beyond reporting attack and
                            burning of headquarters.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>